  "text": "TLS configuration in Prometheus flows from prometheus-common through prometheus's configuration layer to the actual tls.Config used in HTTP clients.\n\n## Core TLS Configuration (prometheus-common)\n\nIn `github.com/prometheus/common/config/http_config.go`:\n\n1. **TLSConfig struct** (lines 328-339): Defines the configuration structure with fields:\n   - CAFile: path to CA certificate file for server certificate verification\n   - CertFile: path to client certificate file\n   - KeyFile: path to client private key file\n   - ServerName: for hostname verification\n   - InsecureSkipVerify: flag to skip certificate verification\n\n2. **NewTLSConfig function** (lines 293-325): Converts TLSConfig struct to Go's *tls.Config by:\n   - Creating a tls.Config with InsecureSkipVerify setting\n   - Loading and parsing CA certificates from CAFile\n   - Setting ServerName for TLS handshake\n   - Loading client certificates and setting GetClientCertificate callback\n   - Handling file validation and error cases\n\n3. **HTTPClientConfig struct** (lines 75-86): Wraps TLSConfig along with:\n   - BasicAuth credentials\n   - BearerToken authentication\n   - Proxy URL settings\n   - TLSConfig field for TLS-specific settings\n\n4. **NewClientFromConfig function** (lines 125-131): Creates HTTP client by calling NewRoundTripperFromConfig\n\n5. **NewRoundTripperFromConfig function** (lines 135-183): Creates HTTP RoundTripper that:\n   - Calls NewTLSConfig to convert the TLSConfig struct to *tls.Config\n   - Passes the tlsConfig to http.Transport's TLSClientConfig field\n   - Wraps with authentication layers (bearer token, basic auth)\n   - Creates tlsRoundTripper for automatic CA file reloading if CAFile is specified\n\n## Configuration Structures (prometheus)\n\nIn `github.com/prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go`:\n\n1. **ScrapeConfig struct** (line 830): Contains HTTPClientConfig field (inline) - used for scrape target configuration\n2. **RemoteWriteConfig struct** (line 1434): Contains HTTPClientConfig field (inline) - used for remote write endpoints\n3. **RemoteReadConfig struct** (line 1597): Contains HTTPClientConfig field (inline) - used for remote read endpoints\n4. **TracingConfig struct** (line 1165): Contains TLSConfig field directly - used for OTLP tracing endpoints\n\n## Application Points\n\n### Scrape Targets\n\nIn `github.com/prometheus/prometheus/scrape/scrape.go`:\n- **newScrapeClient function** (line 2260): Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(cfg, name, optFuncs...)` where cfg is HTTPClientConfig from ScrapeConfig, creating HTTP clients for scraping metrics from targets\n\n### Remote Write/Read\n\nIn `github.com/prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/client.go`:\n- **ClientConfig struct** (lines 128-141): Contains HTTPClientConfig field\n- **NewReadClient function** (line 152): Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(conf.HTTPClientConfig, \"remote_storage_read_client\", optFuncs...)` to create HTTP client for remote read queries\n- **NewWriteClient function** (line 188): Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig(conf.HTTPClientConfig, \"remote_storage_write_client\", httpOpts...)` to create HTTP client for remote write requests\n\n### Tracing (OTLP)\n\nIn `github.com/prometheus/prometheus/tracing/tracing.go`:\n- **buildTracerProvider function** (line 131): Calls getClient with TracingConfig\n- **getClient function** (line 179): Handles both gRPC and HTTP OTLP clients:\n  - For gRPC (line 189): Calls `config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig)` and passes result to `otlptracegrpc.WithTLSCredentials(credentials.NewTLS(tlsConf))`\n  - For HTTP (line 222): Calls `config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig)` and passes result to `otlptracehttp.WithTLSClientConfig(tlsConf)`\n\n## Complete Flow\n\nThe TLS configuration flow is:\n1. YAML configuration is parsed into ScrapeConfig, RemoteWriteConfig, RemoteReadConfig, or TracingConfig structs\n2. Each contains HTTPClientConfig or TLSConfig field with file paths and TLS settings\n3. When creating HTTP clients:\n   - prometheus calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig or config_util.NewTLSConfig\n   - This converts the config struct to *tls.Config by loading certificates and CA files\n   - The *tls.Config is set in http.Transport's TLSClientConfig field\n   - The http.Client uses this transport for all HTTPS connections (scrape targets, remote write/read, tracing)\n4. For scrape and remote storage: HTTPClientConfig flows through NewClientFromConfig → NewRoundTripperFromConfig → NewTLSConfig\n5. For tracing: TLSConfig flows through NewTLSConfig and passed directly to OTLP client creators\n"
}

